# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — Agent Instructions

Global, project-agnostic engineering principles come from this Agent OS
installation's `GLOBAL_AGENTS.md`. They apply here and are not restated.
Read them first if you have not already.

## Project facts

- Read `.agent-os/project-profile.md` for observed facts about this project:
  stack, structure, conventions, and known risk areas.
- Read `.agent-os/command-map.md` for the verified build/test/lint/typecheck
  commands — the allow-list for build/test/state-changing commands. Never
  invent one not listed there. Read-only inspection (`ls`, `cat`, `grep`,
  `find`, `git status`/`log`/`diff`) is out of the map's scope and always
  permitted.

## Active learned rules

- Read `.agent-os/learned-rules.md` before making changes.
- Honor every rule whose `Status:` is `active`. Rules with `Status: candidate`
  are observations, not yet binding — do not treat them as settled.
- If you are corrected during this session, record it in
  `.agent-os/review-feedback-log.md` (see `GLOBAL_AGENTS.md` for the
  promotion rule: 2+ occurrences promotes a candidate to active).

## Safety (non-negotiable)

- No destructive operations (`rm -rf`, force-push, dropping data, schema
  migrations) without explicit user approval.
- Never read, print, log, or commit secrets: `.env` files, keys, tokens,
  credentials.
- Build, test, and any state-changing commands: run only what is
  confirmed in `.agent-os/command-map.md` — do not guess one and call it
  "verified." Read-only inspection (`ls`, `cat`, `grep`, `find`, `git
  status`/`log`/`diff`) is always permitted, including while the map is
  still empty.
- Never mark work done while tests, types, or lint are failing or skipped.

## When something fails

- Log it in `.agent-os/failure-log.md` with the exact command and error.
- Do not hide a failure or report a failing task as a success.
